---
import { AppConfig } from "../../data";
---

<section class="Slide">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="header">
            <h2 class="title">Brand Personality</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
            <p class="content-title">Brand Adjectives</p>
            <ol class="pills">
                <li>Intelligent</li>
                <li>Modern</li>
                <li>Minimalistic</li>
                <li>Professional</li>
                <li>Approachable</li>
            </ol>

            <p class="content-title">If { AppConfig.brand_name } was a person</p>
            <ol class="grid-ol">
                <li>
                    <span>Professional</span>
                    <span>Dressed for the boardroom. Not flashy.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span>Strategic</span>
                    <span>Thinks before building. Plans before pricing.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span>Reliable</span>
                    <span>Delivers on every promise made.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span>Modern</span>
                    <span>Latest tech, current practices.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span>Clear</span>
                    <span>One reading. No ambiguity. Any business owner in any industry should understand immediately.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span>Direct</span>
                    <span>Lead with the outcome. The technical detail is for proposals, not headlines.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span>Confident, not arrogant</span>
                    <span>State the fact. Remove the hedge. "We help" not "We aim to help".</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span>Approachable / Human</span>
                    <span>Speak to people, not audiences. No jargon that requires a dictionary. Plain language. Real conversation.</span>
                </li>
            </ol>

            <p>A sharp, seasoned consultant who grew up in Nairobi — speaks both the language of business strategy and the language of code. They wear clean, confident clothes (not flashy). They get straight to the point. They make you feel capable, not confused.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
